{"word":"εὐαγγελίζομαι","slug":"εὐαγγελίζομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐαγγελίζομαι</b></el> <el>(εὐαγγελίζομαι,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:εὐάγγελος'><el>εὐάγγελος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> <i>to bring good news, announce them</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to proclaim as glad tidings</i>, <el>τὴν βασιλείαν τοῦ Θεοῦ</el> <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to preach the gospel</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to preach the gospel to</i> persons, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>;—so also in <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to have the gospel preached to</i> one, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b>; of the gospel, <i>to be preached</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}